This paper focuses on using sentiment analysis to improve user profiling for gender classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as multi-layer perceptron and long short-term memory, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval and data analysis, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
